org.rakiura.cpn
Class Multiset

java.lang.Object
  java.util.AbstractCollection
      org.rakiura.cpn.Multiset
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable, java.util.Collection
public class Multiset
extends java.util.AbstractCollection

Represents a bag of tokens, a multiset. Actual implementation of a multiset, one of the basic datastructures in JFern Petri nets. Used to store and manipulate tokens. Tokens in JFern are any valid Java object, i.e. any Java object-type datastructure can be treated as a token, and can be inserted and removed from a multiset.

getAny

public java.lang.Object getAny()
Returns a random value from this multiset. This is a convenience method, useful to access a single token value from a multiset. If the multiset has more than one token an arbitrary token is picked.

Returns:
a randomly picked token.

getAny

public java.lang.Object getAny(java.lang.Class type)
Returns a random value from this multiset of a given type. This is a convenience method, useful to access a single token value from a multiset of a given type. If the multiset has more than one token of a given type, token is picked at random.

Parameters:
type - the type of the token to be picked.
Returns:
a randomly picked token.
Since:
3.0

getAny

public Multiset getAny(int aNumber)
Returns n random tokens from this multiset. This is a convenience method, useful to access n tokens from a multiset. If there is not enough tokens in this multiset to fulfill the request null will be returned.

Parameters:
aNumber - a number of randomly selected tokens
Returns:
a multiset with n randomly picked tokens, or null if there is not enough tokens to fulfill the request.

getAny

                       java.lang.Class type)
Returns n random tokens from this multiset, all of a specified type. This is a convenience method, useful to access n tokens from a multiset with a specified type. If the request cannot be fulfilled, null is being returned.

Parameters:
